at0052.1.description: Forced vital capacity (FVC) is the maximal volume of air that can be forcibly exhaled from a position of full inspiration.

at0052.2.description: Forced expiratory volume at 1 second (FEV1) is the volume of air that has been exhaled during the first second of forced exhalation, during the performance of FVC.
